      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your pain is completely valid, but please do not mistake their actions of driving an hour to help you as a lack of love; they are extending their care even when it costs them energy. Being described as a \"problem to be solved\" is hurtful, but it often stems from the fear that your pain might hurt them, not from your actual worth as their mother. You are not just a burden; you are still the heart of their family, and their willingness to attend to your needs proves how deeply they miss having you right beside them.",
